                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/comments/3377838958"
                }
            },
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I'm not sure whether Vim needs the same change, since the issue doesn't reproduce there. Vim also treats `~` as a special character and converts `ADMINI~1` to `^ADMINI\\~1$`, but it later enumerates directories using `FindFirstFileW`. That allows it to match both long names and fall back to short names.\n\nhttps://github.com/vim/vim/blob/3cc8c393030d8fdae75bdbb431cca09234a76479/src/filepath.c#L3713-L3715",
            "commit_id": "b9fe16dacab231ce21e1d73e392ba4206e6d3a47",
            "created_at": "2026-06-09T04:03:40Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -687,7 +687,7 @@ static size_t do_path_expand(garray_T *gap, const char *path, size_t wildoff, in\n       s = p + 1;\n     } else if (path_end >= path + wildoff\n #ifdef MSWIN\n-               && vim_strchr(\"*?[~\", (uint8_t)(*path_end)) != NULL\n+               && vim_strchr(\"*?[\", (uint8_t)(*path_end)) != NULL",
